    "recap_headline": "University of Massachusets Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HARTFORD, Conn. -\nUniversity of Massachusetts baseball fell to Kent State, 14-3, in game one of the weekend series on Friday afternoon at Murren Family Field at DiBenedetto Stadium.\nUMass fell to 5-8 overall on the season and 1-6 in the Mid-American Conference, while Kent State improved to 16-4 overall and 6-1 in the league.\nBraden Sullivan\nled with two hits, which included his first triple of the season and second home run of the year.\nAnthony Tirado\nfollowed with one hit, recording his first collegiate triple. Sullivan scored two runs on the afternoon as Tirado had one.\nReece McCarthy\n, Sullivan and\nRyan Kolben\nall had one RBI each.\nKent State took an early 1-0 lead in the opening frame on a single to center field.\nUMass tied it up in the second at 1-1. With one out, Sullivan tripled to deep center field, before\nMarc Willi\ntook his place on first after being hit by a pitch. Kolben laid down a sacrifice bunt with Sullivan coming across the dish.\nIn the third, Tirado led off with a triple to deep right field. A sacrifice fly with one out from\nReece McCarthy\naided Tirado to cross home plate and give the Minutemen a 2-1 lead. Massachusetts added to its lead in the fourth with a solo home run to deep left field to make it a 3-1 game.\nThe Golden Flashes knotted up the game at three apiece with two runs scored in the sixth, before taking a 6-3 lead with three runs scored in the seventh. The Golden Flashes put up eight more in the top of the eighth to win 14-3.\nGavin Sitarz\n(1-1) took the loss for Massachusetts, tossing one complete inning with five hits, three runs, no walks and two strikeouts.\nGavin Jones (1-1) had the win for Kent State, allowing no runs, no hits, no walks and striking out two in two complete innings of work.\nMassachusetts and Kent State prepare for game two of the series on Saturday, March 21, at 1 p.m. at Murren Family Field/ DiBenedetto Stadium in Hartford, Connecticut.",
    "watch_url": null
  },
